1
00:00:01,559 --> 00:00:05,129
Using the long weekend,
we Detective Boys...

2
00:00:05,196 --> 00:00:07,065
first came to Kyoto.

3
00:00:07,632 --> 00:00:09,534
Kyoto, at last.

4
00:00:09,601 --> 00:00:11,102
I'm so excited!

5
00:00:11,169 --> 00:00:13,004
Yeah!
But still...

6
00:00:13,071 --> 00:00:16,541
we don't board the ship till tomorrow,
so why'd we come a day early?

7
00:00:16,608 --> 00:00:18,009
Well, that's obviously...

8
00:00:18,276 --> 00:00:22,413
since we came all the way to Kyoto,
we want to eat something delicious!

9
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:25,183
Especially Kyoto wagashi.
Right, right!

10
00:00:25,416 --> 00:00:28,586
And sipping local sake
under the night cherry blossoms...

11
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:30,622
Hold on a second.

12
00:00:30,922 --> 00:00:31,990
Listen up.

13
00:00:32,056 --> 00:00:35,260
The reason we came all the way to Kyoto
isn't to drink sake...

14
00:00:35,493 --> 00:00:38,029
and it isn't to eat sweets either.

15
00:00:38,263 --> 00:00:42,133
It's for the experience cruise
on the Aegis ship Hotaka.

16
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,768
You grown-ups...

17
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,870
only came along
to chaperone us.

18
00:00:46,170 --> 00:00:47,906
Even if you say that...

19
00:00:47,972 --> 00:00:50,308
you can still do things
on the side, right?

20
00:00:50,375 --> 00:00:51,442
Right?

21
00:00:51,509 --> 00:00:52,610
Riiight?

22
00:00:52,677 --> 00:00:56,080
(laughs) Which one of us
is the side thing here?

23
00:00:57,849 --> 00:00:59,517
No matter how many times,
it's fine, isn't it?

24
00:00:59,584 --> 00:01:01,619
Love and deduction,
today and tomorrow.

25
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:03,688
The day before the Aegis ship cruise...

26
00:01:03,755 --> 00:01:05,290
a shocking case
we ran into in Kyoto.

27
00:01:05,823 --> 00:01:07,125
Seeing through
the one and only truth.

28
00:01:07,191 --> 00:01:08,993
Looks like a kid,
mind of an adult.

29
00:01:09,060 --> 00:01:11,896
His name is Detective Conan!

30
00:01:28,487 --> 00:01:34,493
♪~

31
00:02:50,169 --> 00:02:55,107
~♪

32
00:02:55,107 --> 00:02:57,770
"Famed Shop's Sweets Disappears".

33
00:03:02,915 --> 00:03:04,750
Into a mold shaped like
the Kyoto bird...

34
00:03:04,816 --> 00:03:09,621
they brush rice oil as a release agent,
then pour in the special batter...

35
00:03:09,688 --> 00:03:12,257
Man, that looks
really tasty.

36
00:03:12,324 --> 00:03:15,160
Not just looks tasty,
it actually is tasty.

37
00:03:15,994 --> 00:03:19,698
Ran tried it at my place
and got completely hooked.

38
00:03:19,765 --> 00:03:22,167
That's why we came
all the way to buy some.

39
00:03:22,234 --> 00:03:25,304
So this was the real goal
all along, huh?

40
00:03:25,370 --> 00:03:27,406
Huh?! No, that's...

41
00:03:28,407 --> 00:03:29,775
What's wrong, Ran?

42
00:03:30,042 --> 00:03:31,376
Listen, Sonoko.

43
00:03:31,643 --> 00:03:33,679
The chocolate flavor
is completely sold out.

44
00:03:33,745 --> 00:03:37,883
Geez... don't scare me like that.
I thought something happened.

45
00:03:37,950 --> 00:03:41,620
But that's the whole reason
we stopped in Kyoto!

46
00:03:41,954 --> 00:03:45,824
But this isn't the only place
that carries the chocolate flavor, right?

47
00:03:45,891 --> 00:03:48,360
That's right.
Besides us...

48
00:03:48,427 --> 00:03:52,831
there's the shops on Arashiyama,
Shiokoji Street, Shinkyogoku, and Shirakawa.

49
00:03:52,898 --> 00:03:54,766
Hey, is it really true?

50
00:03:54,833 --> 00:03:57,069
The chocolate flavor
all vanished?

51
00:03:57,569 --> 00:04:01,106
The chocolate flavor's gone?
What do you mean, gone?

52
00:04:01,406 --> 00:04:02,474
That's right.

53
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:04,743
How did something
like that happen?

54
00:04:05,410 --> 00:04:07,679
That's the thing,
we really don't understand it.

55
00:04:07,746 --> 00:04:08,747
You don't understand?

56
00:04:10,315 --> 00:04:13,552
This morning... the craftsmen
from Umehara...

57
00:04:13,885 --> 00:04:16,855
definitely delivered them, but...

58
00:04:17,356 --> 00:04:22,628
Forty boxes of Ogura, forty of matcha,
and forty of chocolate.

59
00:04:22,694 --> 00:04:24,129
Right, good work.

60
00:04:24,429 --> 00:04:26,965
Well then, let's get them
on display.

61
00:04:45,217 --> 00:04:48,520
Huh? You haven't finished
the display yet?

62
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:50,922
Huh? Why not?

63
00:04:51,757 --> 00:04:55,460
That's strange.
We definitely set them out just now, right?

64
00:04:55,527 --> 00:04:58,797
Yeah... that's odd.

65
00:05:00,465 --> 00:05:03,602
Anyway, we'd better display them quick,
the customers will be here soon.

66
00:05:03,669 --> 00:05:04,670
(drawer opens)

67
00:05:05,170 --> 00:05:08,173
Huh? They're not here.
The chocolate flavor's gone.

68
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,508
Huh?!

69
00:05:09,574 --> 00:05:12,678
Who did this? Where'd they put them?
W-Why?

70
00:05:13,078 --> 00:05:16,281
So now, to get some shared
from the other shops...

71
00:05:16,348 --> 00:05:17,816
the craftsmen are...

72
00:05:18,750 --> 00:05:20,686
Hey, this is a disaster!

73
00:05:20,752 --> 00:05:24,323
The chocolate flavor's gone from
the Shirakawa and Shinkyogoku shops too.

74
00:05:24,389 --> 00:05:26,191
Huh?!

75
00:05:27,826 --> 00:05:31,730
No good. The chocolate flavor's
gone from the Uzumasa shop too.

76
00:05:31,797 --> 00:05:33,865
It's not at the Shiokoji Street one either.

77
00:05:33,932 --> 00:05:35,467
W-What did you say?

78
00:05:35,534 --> 00:05:38,670
So the chocolate flavor vanished
from all five shops?

79
00:05:38,737 --> 00:05:41,406
Th-That's what it
comes down to, yeah.

80
00:05:41,707 --> 00:05:43,542
Something like that...

81
00:05:44,276 --> 00:05:46,411
What's all the racket about?

82
00:05:46,678 --> 00:05:47,913
Uncle.

83
00:05:47,979 --> 00:05:50,349
This is no time to be
rummaging for souvenirs.

84
00:05:50,415 --> 00:05:51,717
It's a case! A case!

85
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:54,720
The sweets that were here
have vanished, apparently.

86
00:05:54,786 --> 00:05:57,689
Listen, I'm a famous detective.

87
00:05:57,756 --> 00:06:00,092
One or two missing sweets...

88
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:01,727
A famous detective?

89
00:06:01,793 --> 00:06:06,531
Yep! This is the renowned
Kogoro Mouri, also known as...

90
00:06:06,598 --> 00:06:07,866
Huh?!

91
00:06:07,933 --> 00:06:09,768
The famous Sleeping Kogoro?

92
00:06:10,202 --> 00:06:14,272
Indeed.
I am the great detective Kogoro Mouri.

93
00:06:14,339 --> 00:06:17,709
Please, we beg you.
Lend us your help.

94
00:06:17,776 --> 00:06:22,280
No, no... I'm about to go enjoy
sake and Kyoto's cherry blossoms.

95
00:06:22,347 --> 00:06:25,283
Don't say that.
Please, we're begging you.

96
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:28,019
That's right, Dad.
It's a huge case.

97
00:06:28,086 --> 00:06:30,389
A-A huge case, you say...

98
00:06:30,455 --> 00:06:32,090
Hey, hey.
Hm?

99
00:06:32,691 --> 00:06:36,094
Isn't that thing on the ceiling
a security camera?

100
00:06:38,163 --> 00:06:42,868
We only have footage from when we
opened the shop at 10 a.m., though.

101
00:06:42,934 --> 00:06:44,269
What's this?

102
00:06:44,336 --> 00:06:47,672
The shelf where the missing sweets were
isn't even in the shot.

103
00:06:47,739 --> 00:06:51,610
Right... the Kyoto bird display
is directly under the camera.

104
00:06:51,877 --> 00:06:56,081
Ah, that's right when we noticed
the chocolate flavor was gone.

105
00:06:56,148 --> 00:07:00,118
After this, everyone searched
the whole shop, but...

106
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:01,520
Pause it for a sec.

107
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:03,588
What is it, Conan-kun?

108
00:07:04,523 --> 00:07:09,327
That person in cherry-blossom pink
in the top-left screen... isn't that a bit odd?

109
00:07:09,795 --> 00:07:10,829
Huh?

110
00:07:11,396 --> 00:07:13,899
Because they got close
to the Kyoto bird shelf?

111
00:07:14,132 --> 00:07:17,402
No matter what, there's no way to steal them
in such a short time.

112
00:07:17,469 --> 00:07:19,471
And besides, this person showed up...

113
00:07:19,538 --> 00:07:21,773
after the chocolate flavor
was already gone.

114
00:07:21,873 --> 00:07:25,610
No, not that.
It's pretty chilly today, right?

115
00:07:25,944 --> 00:07:28,980
For that, isn't this person
dressed awfully light?

116
00:07:29,381 --> 00:07:30,415
Oh...

117
00:07:30,849 --> 00:07:32,918
Now that you mention it,
yeah...

118
00:07:33,218 --> 00:07:36,788
...wait, who cares
about something like that.

119
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:40,659
Well, well.
And who might this be...

120
00:07:41,059 --> 00:07:42,928
Isn't that Mouri-han?

121
00:07:43,161 --> 00:07:44,196
Hm...

122
00:07:44,930 --> 00:07:45,931
Who?

123
00:07:46,331 --> 00:07:49,301
You're Inspector Ayanokoji
of the Kyoto Prefectural Police, right?

124
00:07:49,668 --> 00:07:52,804
Heh. So what's an inspector
doing in a place like this?

125
00:07:52,871 --> 00:07:55,941
Well, I'm off duty today...

126
00:07:56,007 --> 00:07:58,176
so I was taking this little one for a walk.
- "Ayanokōji Fumimaro, Kyoto Prefectural Police,
Criminal Investigation Division, Inspector.

127
00:07:58,477 --> 00:07:59,878
Huh, I see.

128
00:08:00,178 --> 00:08:03,048
Do chipmunks
even need walks?

129
00:08:03,114 --> 00:08:04,216
Who knows...

130
00:08:04,282 --> 00:08:07,285
...I mean, that's not really
much of a walk anyway.

131
00:08:07,619 --> 00:08:11,122
Anyway, you came at a good time.
It's a theft case.

132
00:08:11,189 --> 00:08:13,959
This is a job for the police.
I'll leave the rest to you.

133
00:08:14,192 --> 00:08:15,193
Huh?

134
00:08:16,728 --> 00:08:18,930
We're truly sorry.

135
00:08:18,997 --> 00:08:21,333
We'll have stock again tomorrow.

136
00:08:21,666 --> 00:08:24,569
It's not even noon yet
and you're sold out...

137
00:08:24,636 --> 00:08:26,137
isn't that a bit early?

138
00:08:26,204 --> 00:08:28,340
We were really
looking forward to it.

139
00:08:28,573 --> 00:08:30,809
The chocolate-flavored Kyoto bird.

140
00:08:32,577 --> 00:08:36,214
Um... can't you make
the chocolate flavor right now?

141
00:08:36,281 --> 00:08:40,018
Today's chocolate has all
been used up already, I'm afraid.

142
00:08:40,452 --> 00:08:44,523
The chocolate we use for that flavor
isn't made in-house...

143
00:08:44,589 --> 00:08:47,993
we purchase carefully selected
chocolate from overseas.

144
00:08:48,059 --> 00:08:51,763
Tomorrow's batch won't arrive
until tomorrow.

145
00:08:51,830 --> 00:08:54,699
So the chocolate flavor's
on hold till tomorrow, huh.

146
00:08:54,766 --> 00:08:55,767
Yeah...

147
00:08:56,201 --> 00:08:59,271
No, it had to be today.

148
00:08:59,538 --> 00:09:02,774
"It had to be today"?
Why's that?

149
00:09:03,275 --> 00:09:05,911
Today is the anniversary
of the former president's death.

150
00:09:05,977 --> 00:09:07,212
Oh...

151
00:09:07,612 --> 00:09:11,550
That's why we wanted to launch
the new product today, but...

152
00:09:11,616 --> 00:09:14,719
I'm sorry,
we've sold out.

153
00:09:14,786 --> 00:09:18,223
Sold out, she says.
Huh? Already?

154
00:09:19,024 --> 00:09:23,728
Ugh... above all, I feel awful for the customers
who were looking forward to it.

155
00:09:26,464 --> 00:09:27,966
Is that so? Really?

156
00:09:29,034 --> 00:09:31,670
I see. Understood.

157
00:09:32,737 --> 00:09:35,140
I asked a fellow detective
to do me a favor...

158
00:09:35,206 --> 00:09:38,643
and had him canvass
at the Uzumasa shop, and...

159
00:09:38,977 --> 00:09:41,079
The shop that carries
the Kyoto bird?

160
00:09:41,146 --> 00:09:44,783
Yes. Turns out, when the
chocolate flavor went missing...

161
00:09:44,849 --> 00:09:48,987
someone saw a suspicious car
parked in front of the shop.

162
00:09:49,054 --> 00:09:52,157
A suspicious car?
What model and plate number?

163
00:09:52,223 --> 00:09:54,092
A cherry-blossom-pink compact car.

164
00:09:54,159 --> 00:09:56,328
But they couldn't make out
the model or the plate.

165
00:09:57,128 --> 00:10:00,465
A pink compact car alone
isn't much to go on...

166
00:10:00,532 --> 00:10:02,267
Um...

167
00:10:02,500 --> 00:10:05,670
I saw a pink compact car too.

168
00:10:05,737 --> 00:10:07,372
What?
Huh?

169
00:10:07,439 --> 00:10:09,107
You saw it? When?

170
00:10:09,374 --> 00:10:12,210
Let's see, that was, um...

171
00:10:13,712 --> 00:10:16,748
When the chocolate flavor vanished
and we were searching for it.

172
00:10:16,815 --> 00:10:18,283
You saw it too?

173
00:10:18,350 --> 00:10:21,119
Yeah, it was parked
in front of the shop.

174
00:10:21,386 --> 00:10:23,088
But still...

175
00:10:23,154 --> 00:10:26,024
if we could at least
get the plate number...

176
00:10:26,491 --> 00:10:28,860
Then why not ask
the other shops too?

177
00:10:28,927 --> 00:10:29,995
Huh?

178
00:10:30,261 --> 00:10:33,398
I mean, if the person in that car
is the culprit...

179
00:10:33,465 --> 00:10:36,234
they might've been spotted
at the other shops too, right?

180
00:10:36,301 --> 00:10:39,137
Then send some people out
to ask around.

181
00:10:39,204 --> 00:10:41,473
H-Hold on a moment, please.

182
00:10:41,539 --> 00:10:45,777
If you need that much manpower,
ask the local theft division.

183
00:10:45,844 --> 00:10:48,113
I'm off duty, you know.

184
00:10:48,179 --> 00:10:50,482
Don't sweat
the small stuff.

185
00:10:50,548 --> 00:10:52,884
I'll go to the
Shiokoji Street shop.

186
00:10:52,951 --> 00:10:53,952
Huh?

187
00:10:54,019 --> 00:10:56,454
If we dawdle,
they'll get away.

188
00:10:56,521 --> 00:10:58,556
Then I'll take Shinkyogoku.

189
00:10:58,623 --> 00:10:59,624
Yeah.

190
00:10:59,924 --> 00:11:02,293
Dad, you take the last one,
the Shirakawa shop.

191
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,361
Huh?!

192
00:11:03,828 --> 00:11:07,298
Ayanokoji-san, you stay here
and wait for everyone to call in.

193
00:11:07,365 --> 00:11:08,867
Huh, me too?

194
00:11:09,334 --> 00:11:10,702
Listen up, you guys.

195
00:11:10,769 --> 00:11:14,839
Ayumi, go with big sister Ran.
Genta, with big sister Sonoko.

196
00:11:14,906 --> 00:11:17,142
Mitsuhiko, you go
with the old man.

197
00:11:17,709 --> 00:11:19,444
The suspect's plate number...

198
00:11:19,511 --> 00:11:22,847
even in pieces, draw it out of them
and report back to me.

199
00:11:22,914 --> 00:11:24,149
Got it.
Understood.

200
00:11:24,582 --> 00:11:27,085
I'll piece it all together.

201
00:11:36,248 --> 00:11:38,717
It's a cherry-blossom-pink
compact car...

202
00:11:38,784 --> 00:11:43,055
Ah, now that you mention it,
it was parked in front of the shop.

203
00:11:43,122 --> 00:11:45,324
Really? The plate number?

204
00:11:45,391 --> 00:11:48,027
Ah, I didn't get
that far, sorry...

205
00:11:48,093 --> 00:11:51,597
Even a little is fine.
If you remember any of the numbers, tell me.

206
00:11:51,930 --> 00:11:53,632
Even if you ask me that...

207
00:11:53,699 --> 00:11:56,402
I'm pretty sure
it was a Shiromi plate.

208
00:11:56,468 --> 00:11:58,871
Wow!
Thank you so much!

209
00:11:59,138 --> 00:12:00,906
Yeah, I saw it, I saw it.

210
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:03,509
It was a Shiromi plate, I think...

211
00:12:03,575 --> 00:12:06,912
and I remember it started
with "11."

212
00:12:07,279 --> 00:12:09,148
Starts with 11.

213
00:12:09,448 --> 00:12:13,552
But still, for it to vanish
from every single shop...

214
00:12:13,619 --> 00:12:15,921
Do you have any idea
what could've caused it?

215
00:12:17,156 --> 00:12:20,759
It might be a curse
from the late former president.

216
00:12:20,826 --> 00:12:22,728
Eek...

217
00:12:24,163 --> 00:12:26,198
Conan-kun, this is Mitsuhiko.

218
00:12:26,665 --> 00:12:29,401
About the plate number,
all I could find out...

219
00:12:29,468 --> 00:12:32,471
was that there was an 8
near the end.

220
00:12:32,771 --> 00:12:34,707
An 8 near the end.

221
00:12:34,773 --> 00:12:35,808
Got it.

222
00:12:36,141 --> 00:12:37,209
I see.

223
00:12:37,276 --> 00:12:41,413
A pink compact car, and we've got
this much of the plate...

224
00:12:41,714 --> 00:12:44,717
We might be able to run
a registered-owner check now.

225
00:12:52,091 --> 00:12:54,626
We've identified the owner
of the spotted car.

226
00:12:54,693 --> 00:12:55,694
Huh?

227
00:12:55,961 --> 00:13:00,065
Mako Kawasumi, 22,
living in Shiromi, Osaka City.

228
00:13:00,132 --> 00:13:01,967
Does that name
ring any bells?

229
00:13:02,334 --> 00:13:04,470
No.
Not at all.

230
00:13:04,937 --> 00:13:07,172
It's the first time
I've heard it.

231
00:13:07,239 --> 00:13:10,943
I see. Anyway, we're using
the N-System right now...

232
00:13:11,009 --> 00:13:13,479
to track down
that car's location.

233
00:13:13,545 --> 00:13:14,580
Right.

234
00:13:15,914 --> 00:13:18,450
Hey, you kids...

235
00:13:18,517 --> 00:13:19,885
Conan, you eat too.

236
00:13:19,952 --> 00:13:22,721
Big sister Sonoko
bought these for us.

237
00:13:22,788 --> 00:13:25,657
(giggles)
The matcha flavor's delicious!

238
00:13:25,891 --> 00:13:30,162
Right? I got hooked on the Kyoto bird
through the matcha flavor too.

239
00:13:30,529 --> 00:13:34,566
But you know, it seems the former president
wasn't fond of it.

240
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,535
Huh?
Hm?

241
00:13:37,269 --> 00:13:40,572
Originally, the Kyoto bird
only came in Ogura flavor...

242
00:13:40,639 --> 00:13:44,410
and the matcha flavor was launched
under the current president.

243
00:13:44,676 --> 00:13:47,713
Huh. But since the matcha
got such good reviews...

244
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:50,115
that's why they decided to put out
a chocolate flavor too, right?

245
00:13:50,182 --> 00:13:54,186
Yeah... but a craftsman
over at Shinkyogoku said...

246
00:13:54,453 --> 00:13:58,290
"If the old president heard about a chocolate flavor,
he'd drop dead from the shock."

247
00:13:58,357 --> 00:14:00,225
...or something like that.

248
00:14:00,292 --> 00:14:04,229
So you know,
maybe this is...

249
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:06,298
a cuuurse!

250
00:14:06,365 --> 00:14:09,368
Eek! Stop it, Sonoko!

251
00:14:09,435 --> 00:14:11,437
Gyaah...
(thud)

252
00:14:11,503 --> 00:14:13,439
Huh?
Ah...

253
00:14:13,505 --> 00:14:17,576
Ow ow ow... I forgot how much
Ran hates ghost stuff.

254
00:14:17,643 --> 00:14:18,710
Ah, sorry...

255
00:14:18,777 --> 00:14:21,413
(laughs)... hm?

256
00:14:25,284 --> 00:14:26,752
Inspector Ayanokoji.

257
00:14:27,019 --> 00:14:30,389
Ah, Detective Kurumazaki.
Good work.

258
00:14:30,656 --> 00:14:32,691
The suspect's car
was photographed...

259
00:14:32,758 --> 00:14:34,326
ten minutes ago by...

260
00:14:34,393 --> 00:14:36,995
the N-System camera
on Marutamachi Street.

261
00:14:37,563 --> 00:14:39,998
That's near
the Shirakawa shop.

262
00:14:40,065 --> 00:14:41,133
Yes.

263
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:43,502
And this is the photo.

264
00:14:45,504 --> 00:14:47,940
Huh?
This is...

265
00:14:50,509 --> 00:14:52,578
The person in cherry-blossom pink...

266
00:14:53,579 --> 00:14:56,615
Mitsuhiko, are you still
at the Shirakawa shop?

267
00:14:56,849 --> 00:14:59,885
We're here. Mr. Mouri...

268
00:14:59,952 --> 00:15:03,121
started drinking sake
and won't budge.

269
00:15:03,388 --> 00:15:07,125
Pwah! (laughs)

270
00:15:07,192 --> 00:15:09,528
Ahh... so there you go.

271
00:15:09,862 --> 00:15:11,930
Hmm...

272
00:15:12,531 --> 00:15:15,767
That drunkard!

273
00:15:15,834 --> 00:15:17,536
W-Where are you going, Ran?

274
00:15:17,836 --> 00:15:20,305
To grab him by the scruff
and drag him back.

275
00:15:20,372 --> 00:15:23,141
Ah, it's gonna rain blood...

276
00:15:23,208 --> 00:15:24,409
Yeah...

277
00:15:24,476 --> 00:15:27,579
Hey, ma'am,
what are you doing with that?

278
00:15:27,646 --> 00:15:29,381
Ah, this?

279
00:15:29,448 --> 00:15:32,618
This part's gone soggy,
so I've got to swap it out.

280
00:15:32,684 --> 00:15:34,620
Ah, that's from earlier...

281
00:15:34,686 --> 00:15:39,358
Ugh... above all, I feel awful for the customers
who were looking forward to it.

282
00:15:42,227 --> 00:15:44,296
Hey, let me see that
for a sec.

283
00:15:46,698 --> 00:15:51,503
Look, this is the Ogura-flavor Kyoto bird
they pulled from below to restock.

284
00:15:51,803 --> 00:15:55,741
This one's the Ogura Kyoto bird being swapped out,
gone soggy from tears.

285
00:15:55,807 --> 00:15:59,811
And this is the Ogura Kyoto bird
that was displayed underneath it.

286
00:16:00,178 --> 00:16:02,247
Doesn't this look
a little smudged?

287
00:16:03,382 --> 00:16:06,818
Maybe it ended up like that
when they stuck the label on?

288
00:16:06,885 --> 00:16:10,422
But look, the area around the label
on this one pulled out for restocking...

289
00:16:10,856 --> 00:16:12,357
isn't smudged at all.

290
00:16:12,991 --> 00:16:15,427
Conan-kun,
what's bothering you?

291
00:16:15,994 --> 00:16:17,696
Maybe I've been...

292
00:16:18,063 --> 00:16:21,199
making one heck of
a mistaken assumption.

293
00:16:22,501 --> 00:16:24,436
Hey, mister.

294
00:16:24,670 --> 00:16:27,773
Let's head back to
Conan-kun and the others now.

295
00:16:27,839 --> 00:16:29,441
Pwah, ha.

296
00:16:29,975 --> 00:16:34,513
Come oooon, don't rush me.
(chuckles)

297
00:16:34,580 --> 00:16:37,316
It's not even
a big case.

298
00:16:37,382 --> 00:16:40,953
Oh? "Not even
a big case"?

299
00:16:41,019 --> 00:16:42,220
Hello there!

300
00:16:42,287 --> 00:16:46,558
Yeah, yeah, not even a big
ca... se?

301
00:16:47,459 --> 00:16:51,930
Out flower-viewing
in the middle of a case... you've got some nerve.

302
00:16:52,197 --> 00:16:56,435
N-No, w-w-wait, Ran!
You've got it wrong, I...

303
00:16:56,501 --> 00:16:58,770
(smack)
Th-the cherry blossoms!

304
00:16:58,837 --> 00:17:00,872
It's the cherry blossoms' fault!

305
00:17:00,939 --> 00:17:01,940
Hm?

306
00:17:02,941 --> 00:17:03,942
That person...

307
00:17:04,943 --> 00:17:06,912
Um, excuse me.

308
00:17:06,979 --> 00:17:08,947
You've been to
all of the shops, haven't you?

309
00:17:09,348 --> 00:17:11,950
Every shop that carries
the Kyoto bird.

310
00:17:12,017 --> 00:17:15,887
Huh... why? Why do you ask?

311
00:17:16,521 --> 00:17:20,826
At every one of them, the chocolate
flavor of the Kyoto bird has vanished.

312
00:17:20,892 --> 00:17:23,395
Uh... eek!

313
00:17:24,196 --> 00:17:26,665
Mouri-han, Mouri-han.

314
00:17:26,965 --> 00:17:31,169
Mouri-han, h-huh?
Mouri-han's not back yet?

315
00:17:31,403 --> 00:17:35,140
Ah... the old man, he said
he'd be back soon.

316
00:17:35,207 --> 00:17:36,808
So, how did it go?

317
00:17:36,875 --> 00:17:41,213
Ah, just like Mouri-han
said on the phone...

318
00:17:41,279 --> 00:17:44,216
something strange
was detected from here.

319
00:17:44,282 --> 00:17:46,618
You mean, could it be...?
Hm?

320
00:17:47,886 --> 00:17:51,456
Huh? That's right.
How did you know?

321
00:17:51,523 --> 00:17:55,093
Ah... the old man, Kogoro,
figured it might be that.

322
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:58,764
Well, well.
As expected of the great detective.

323
00:17:59,698 --> 00:18:01,633
Ah, Mouri-han.

324
00:18:01,700 --> 00:18:03,135
Ugh...

325
00:18:04,636 --> 00:18:07,873
(snoring)
Huh?

326
00:18:11,543 --> 00:18:13,545
What happened to him,
Mouri-han?

327
00:18:13,612 --> 00:18:15,147
Ah... the drunk...

328
00:18:15,213 --> 00:18:18,417
I gave him a little punishment
and he ended up like this.

329
00:18:18,483 --> 00:18:20,318
Please, don't mind it
at all.

330
00:18:20,385 --> 00:18:21,620
A "little," she says...

331
00:18:21,953 --> 00:18:24,623
(laughs)
Well, this is good timing.

332
00:18:24,856 --> 00:18:27,859
Huh? Come to think of it,
where's my Kurumazaki...

333
00:18:27,926 --> 00:18:32,330
Ah, the old man Kogoro asked him
to do something over the phone earlier.

334
00:18:32,564 --> 00:18:33,565
Oh.

335
00:18:34,366 --> 00:18:38,070
Mouri-han, what did you
ask Kurumazaki to do?

336
00:18:38,804 --> 00:18:42,574
More importantly, Inspector Ayanokoji,
did you look into it?

337
00:18:43,008 --> 00:18:46,511
The packaging of the Ogura flavor
that was on display.

338
00:18:46,578 --> 00:18:51,349
Yes. Rice oil was found
around the Ogura-flavor labels.

339
00:18:51,416 --> 00:18:53,351
Huh?
Huh? Rice oil?

340
00:18:53,418 --> 00:18:57,723
Rice oil... we use that
as a release agent.

341
00:18:57,989 --> 00:18:59,558
Ah...

342
00:18:59,624 --> 00:19:02,060
Hey, what's a release agent?

343
00:19:02,294 --> 00:19:05,697
Ah, before baking the batter,
you brush it on the mold...

344
00:19:05,764 --> 00:19:08,567
it's an oil that makes it easy
to get the batter out of the mold.

345
00:19:08,867 --> 00:19:11,336
But why was it...

346
00:19:11,403 --> 00:19:13,438
on the Ogura labels?

347
00:19:13,839 --> 00:19:15,707
It wasn't simply on them.

348
00:19:16,141 --> 00:19:17,776
It was applied there.

349
00:19:18,410 --> 00:19:20,712
Before the Ogura labels
were stuck on.

350
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:26,418
Forty boxes of Ogura, forty of matcha,
and forty of chocolate.

351
00:19:26,485 --> 00:19:27,953
Right, good work.

352
00:19:28,186 --> 00:19:30,756
Well then, let's get them
on display.

353
00:19:32,891 --> 00:19:36,962
The first ones put on display
were ten boxes of each.

354
00:19:37,195 --> 00:19:40,732
So they only needed to tamper
with ten boxes of chocolate.

355
00:19:41,266 --> 00:19:42,634
With cotton soaked
in rice oil...

356
00:19:42,701 --> 00:19:45,771
hidden in their palms, they traced
over the chocolate labels...

357
00:19:45,837 --> 00:19:47,606
and peeled the labels off.

358
00:19:47,672 --> 00:19:50,609
Then they stuck fresh
Ogura labels on top.

359
00:19:50,675 --> 00:19:52,244
Two people, ten boxes...

360
00:19:52,644 --> 00:19:56,882
The ten boxes of Ogura first on display
went into the restocking drawer...

361
00:19:57,115 --> 00:20:00,252
and the ten relabeled Ogura boxes
were slid into their place.

362
00:20:00,619 --> 00:20:03,188
In other words, in this shop, no...

363
00:20:04,055 --> 00:20:07,993
in all five shops, there was no
chocolate flavor from the very start.

364
00:20:08,059 --> 00:20:10,662
Huh?!

365
00:20:10,929 --> 00:20:12,497
Detective Mouri.

366
00:20:12,931 --> 00:20:13,999
Kurumazaki-han.

367
00:20:14,432 --> 00:20:19,137
Just as Detective Mouri said,
in the fridge at the Umehara workshop...

368
00:20:19,204 --> 00:20:21,640
the chocolate that was supposed
to be used today...

369
00:20:21,706 --> 00:20:23,642
was sitting there untouched.

370
00:20:23,708 --> 00:20:24,910
Hm?

371
00:20:24,976 --> 00:20:29,181
In other words, no chocolate flavor
was made today to begin with.

372
00:20:29,648 --> 00:20:31,750
And the only ones
who could pull that off...

373
00:20:32,651 --> 00:20:34,920
are you confectioners.

374
00:20:34,986 --> 00:20:36,288
Huh?!

375
00:20:39,024 --> 00:20:40,692
Why would you do
such a thing?

376
00:20:40,759 --> 00:20:42,627
(sobbing)

377
00:20:42,694 --> 00:20:46,932
The former president
truly hated the matcha flavor.

378
00:20:47,966 --> 00:20:50,502
And a chocolate flavor,
all the more...

379
00:20:50,802 --> 00:20:52,003
Over something like that...

380
00:20:52,070 --> 00:20:54,072
It's not just "something like that"!

381
00:20:54,639 --> 00:20:57,008
It's not just "something like that"...

382
00:20:57,242 --> 00:20:59,978
That's exactly why,
on the former president's death anniversary...

383
00:21:00,045 --> 00:21:03,281
we just couldn't bear
to sell the chocolate flavor.

384
00:21:03,348 --> 00:21:07,352
But we never thought
it would blow up this big...

385
00:21:07,419 --> 00:21:09,387
We're terribly sorry.

386
00:21:09,454 --> 00:21:15,460
(craftsmen sobbing)

387
00:21:17,295 --> 00:21:23,301
♪~

388
00:22:30,635 --> 00:22:36,641
~♪

389
00:22:40,679 --> 00:22:43,782
Are you sure?
Not filing a complaint?

390
00:22:43,848 --> 00:22:48,520
What the former president left behind
is the skill of those craftsmen.

391
00:22:48,586 --> 00:22:49,654
I see.

392
00:22:49,721 --> 00:22:52,924
Um... what's going to happen
with the chocolate flavor?

393
00:22:53,191 --> 00:22:57,062
We won't sell the matcha or chocolate
on the former president's anniversary.

394
00:22:57,128 --> 00:23:00,065
Not until the craftsmen themselves
say they want to.

395
00:23:01,666 --> 00:23:05,770
But I came to love the Kyoto bird
through the matcha flavor, you know.

396
00:23:06,404 --> 00:23:07,772
Thank you kindly.

397
00:23:09,841 --> 00:23:12,510
Huh? Come to think of it,
Mitsuhiko...

398
00:23:12,777 --> 00:23:14,646
Heey, everyone!

399
00:23:14,913 --> 00:23:18,116
Mitsuhiko, what were you
even doing?

400
00:23:18,183 --> 00:23:21,653
Ah, sorry.
The thing is...

401
00:23:22,220 --> 00:23:25,423
Huh... why? Why do you ask?

402
00:23:26,091 --> 00:23:31,296
A-At every one of them, the chocolate
flavor of the Kyoto bird has vanished.

403
00:23:31,363 --> 00:23:32,931
Eek!

404
00:23:33,231 --> 00:23:36,968
That's right.
There's no chocolate flavor anywhere.

405
00:23:37,035 --> 00:23:38,169
Huh?

406
00:23:38,570 --> 00:23:40,605
This is already
the fifth shop...

407
00:23:40,672 --> 00:23:45,043
I've searched this hard,
so why isn't there any?!

408
00:23:45,110 --> 00:23:48,713
(laughs)
Isn't that just like Ran?

409
00:23:51,695 --> 00:23:54,295
"Next Episode"

410
00:23:54,295 --> 00:23:57,595
I wonder where Kengo disappeared to though.

411
00:23:57,595 --> 00:24:00,095
Okay, shall we all go then?

412
00:24:06,995 --> 00:24:10,295
Ridiculous! It can't be.

413
00:24:10,295 --> 00:24:12,295
He couldn't be dead.

414
00:24:12,295 --> 00:24:16,195
Hey! What do you mean by he couldn't be dead?

415
00:24:16,195 --> 00:24:17,795
Next Conan,

416
00:24:17,795 --> 00:24:20,695
"A Rose in a Vineyard".

417
00:24:37,295 --> 00:24:39,495
Next Conan's Hint:

418
00:24:39,495 --> 00:24:41,995
"Type of grape".

419
00:24:41,995 --> 00:24:43,395
The movie will start today!

420
00:24:43,395 --> 00:24:44,995
The Sleeping Kogoro is the star of the movie!

421
00:24:44,995 --> 00:24:46,395
You never learn.
